This app is a self-contained ActivityPub <-> A2A gateway, deliberately NOT bundled
into apps/matrix-a2a-bridge, so the mautrix bridge stays AGPL-free and homeserver-
portable (docs/adr/0014-activitypub-second-federation-transport.md).

It embeds the following third-party components, all under permissive licenses:

  - github.com/go-ap/activitypub        MIT
  - github.com/a2aproject/a2a-go        Apache-2.0
  - github.com/caarlos0/env             MIT
  - github.com/prometheus/client_golang Apache-2.0
  - github.com/gowebpki/jcs             Apache-2.0
  - github.com/mr-tron/base58           MIT
  - gopkg.in/yaml.v3                    MIT / Apache-2.0

No AGPL dependency is present. Never add one: reaching kagent is done through the
same a2a-go client the bridge uses, over agentgateway, so no agent holds a model
credential.
